Krad Link 2

Network A/V Transmitter/Receiver

1.0 Features / Guide


Krad Link is a program used primarly for streaming WebM from a webcam to an Icecast server.

Example:

Use defaults to send a WebM stream:
krad_link --password secretkode deimos.kradradio.com/my_fun_stream.webm

Set Width, height and frames per second options:
krad_link --password secretkode --width 640 --height 360 --fps 10 http://deimos.kradradio.com/my_fun_stream.webm

Don't open the video preview window:
krad_link --password secretkode --nowindow http://deimos.kradradio.com/my_fun_stream.webm

Daemonize:
krad_link --password secretkode --daemon http://deimos.kradradio.com/my_fun_stream.webm

Print lots of interesting information:
krad_link --password secretkode --verbose http://deimos.kradradio.com/my_fun_stream.webm

Record to a file:
krad_link ~/Videos/my_recording.webm

Playback an existing file:
krad_link ~/Videos/my_recording.webm

Use JACK:
krad_link --jack ~/Videos/my_jacked_recording.webm

Use Pulse Audio:
krad_link --pulse ~/Videos/my_pulsed_recording.webm




